body.description: This pre-owned Refurbished product Samsung Galaxy S20 FE 5G has been professionally inspected and tested to work and look like new. When a customer buys a new product and returns or trades it in for a newer or different model this product becomes part of Amazon Renewed or pre-owned, refurbished products. It is carefully inspected and tested to work and look like new by Amazon-qualified suppliers. Galaxy S20 FE is the phone that leaves compromise behind, delivering the innovations of Galaxy S20 5G to make incredible technology available to all. 5G isn’t just fast—it's HyperFast. When you're connected to the network with Galaxy S20 FE 5G, you can game on in real-time with little lag, download at lightning-fast speeds, and experience crystal clear video calls. The phone that thinks faster than fast Take full advantage of fast data speeds and cloud-based content with our latest S20 chipset innovation and 6GB of RAM. Plus, the enhanced NPU takes performance to a new level, so switching from app to app is seamless, live streams come through clear and you've got power enabling you to game on to victory. Space for thousands of photos and videos with 128GB built-in and the ability to store up to 1TB more on a micro SD card.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It's hard for me to write an objective review for this phone. I bought it to replace my Samsung Galaxy Note 10+ that I dropped one too many times. I just couldn't afford another Note right now. This phone was much less expensive. But, I've not had any problems with it. It has more features than most at this price. Everything works like it should.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excellent Condition and Great Phone
reviews.reviewText: This phone arrived on time and in excellent condition. You would think it’s a brand new phone and never used.I’ve been shopping for an unlocked Samsung Galaxy phone for a while. The Samsung Galaxy S20 FE is one of the best you can get around $200. It will update to Android 13. If this seller has more, I highly suggest you buy it.The only thing (and this is not the seller’s or manufacturer’s fault), is that the S20 FE is not compatible on Spectrum Mobile. Why? I have no idea when the S20, S21, S22, S23, A54, A71, A72….and more are compatible with Spectrum.So if you’re looking to use it with Spectrum Mobile, save yourself, and the seller’s time and a headache and go with the S20 or A71. Both have excellent specs for around $200 and Spectrum compatible.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 30, 2023
reviews.reviewText: My old Samsung A14 died and l order a refurbished Samsung S20FE with "Excellent conditon" from this vendor. So far, this phone has not worked well for me.1) It has a small chip in the middle of the sceen. I put a screen protector and covered the chip.2) The phone only works outside of my house but not inside of my house. I would be on the phone talking, l need to stay close tooo my windows. If l walk around, the phone call could drop. There were times, l had to keep calling back to be connected.3) l only transfered my applications to this phone, already, it tells me l am running out of space.There are some serious problems with this phone. I am requesting for a replacement phone.

reviews.reviewerName: I'm so passed off...everything was working perfectly until I had to do  a hard data reset because the pictures I took to test the camera wouldn't delete...  wouldn't delete I Googled why they wouldn't delete and it said it was because it was probably connected to another device...did the safe mode reset and now I can't make any calls...automatically hangs up as soon as they answer...same as when I get an incoming call...internet and text work fine just the calls drop as soon as they are answered...seems shady as f to me...my pics were saving to another device that couldn't be deleted...hope they didn't get my cashapp info too

reviews.reviewText: Had a long message that somehow got deleted...hard data reset disables the call feature somehow but internet and text still works
